# Post-push GitHub Actions (mandatory when applicable)

Source: [cursor-universal-rule](https://github.com/wangyuanzhong/cursor-universal-rule).

## Opt-out

- **Local Desktop only**: if `.cursor/.local-skip-post-push-ci` exists → **skip entire rule**.
- Cloud Agent: **never** skip unless user explicitly disables CI monitoring for this task.

## When this applies

- You ran **`git push`**, or
- You will mark work **done** / open or update a PR and commits are (or will be) on the remote.

If the latest push **did not trigger** any workflow (check `.github/workflows/*.yml` path filters), say so and skip watching.

## What to watch

Only runs **triggered by the latest push** on the **current branch**. Do not chase old SHAs or unrelated branches.

```bash
gh run list --branch "$(git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD)" --limit 10
gh run watch --exit-status
```

For this repo, **Windows** jobs must pass — **`build-windows` / App.Tests** and **Build release EXE** when path filters match. Ubuntu-only green is **not** enough.

## If something is red

1. `gh run view <run-id> --log-failed` — first real error.
2. Fix in repo (code, tests, workflows) → commit → **push** → watch again.
3. Loop: **push → wait → fix → push** until all triggered runs are green or a stop condition hits.

## Fixes must not violate project docs

Before applying a CI-driven fix, cross-check:

- Root `README.md`, `docs/**/*.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, and app-bundled `.txt` specs.
- **Do not** change documented functionality or UI strings to satisfy a test unless you **also** update those docs in the same change set.
- **Do not** weaken tests to greenwash behavior that docs promise to users.

If CI and docs conflict, follow priority in `00-universal-core.mdc` (docs + user intent first, then deliberate code/doc alignment).

## Stop conditions

| Stop | Reason |
|------|--------|
| All triggered runs **success** | Report run IDs. |
| Not fixable in repo | Secrets, billing, permissions — report; no empty commits. |
| Same failure after **2** fix-and-push rounds | Escalate with logs. |
| Required **Windows** job cannot run here | Report; do not claim full CI green. |

